-- 
Taiwan Stocks: AU Optronics, Pegatron, Taichung Commercial

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-03-31T06:21:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/au-optronics-pegatron-yang-ming-marine-taiwan-stock-preview.html
Stocks of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Taiwan  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 1:30 p.m. close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index rose 36.99, or 0.4 percent, to 8,683.30,
the highest close since March 9. The gauge dropped 3.2 percent
this quarter, the first drop since the three months ended June
30, 2010.  AU Optronics Corp. (2409)  (2409 TT), Taiwan’s second-largest maker
of liquefied-crystal displays, jumped 4.9 percent to NT$25.70,
the steepest advance since Sept. 29. Apple Inc. ordered panels
for its iPad2 devices from AU Optronics, the Economic Daily News
reported, without saying where it got the information from.
Yawen Hsiao, a spokeswoman for AU, declined to comment on the
report, saying the company never comments on customers and
orders.  Pegatron Corp. (4938)  (4938 TT), the producer of motherboards and
desktop computers, gained 2.5 percent to NT$33.25, the most in
one week. The company plans to invest additional $35 million in
an electrical plating company in  China ’s Suzhou city through its
subsidiaries, the Taipei-based company said in statement to the
Taiwan stock exchange.  Taichung Commercial Bank (2812)  Co. (2812 TT), a lender, fell 1.2
percent to NT$12.50, the lowest close since March 18. The bank’s
board of directors approved plans to sell NT$2.8 billion of
three-year zero-coupon bonds convertible into shares, the lender
said in a statement to the Taiwan stock exchange. The bank also
plans to sell up to 500 million shares in a private placement,
according to a separate statement. The proceeds will be used to
boost its capital adequacy ratio, and replenish working capital,
it said.  -- With assistance from Janet Ong in Taipei. Editor: Richard
